            "text": "Gram per Square Metre Pascal Second",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Gram per square metre pascal second (g m^-2 Pa^-1 s^-1) is a unit of vapour permeance that expresses mass flow per unit area per unit pressure difference, per unit time. It is the non-prefixed form obtained by removing the Nano prefix from the mass term of the original prefixed unit. In SI terms, 1 g m^-2 Pa^-1 s^-1 corresponds to 1e-3 kg m^-2 Pa^-1 s^-1.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
